1. ID is dynamic (changes every page load) - Use Partial matches
2. If ID does not exist - Use other Attributes other attributes like [name='car'], [class='form-input']
3. Attribute Style [id = xxx] is a powerful way
4. Use #idname for fixed ID's
Example:
<input id="bmwradio_123" type="radio" name="car" value="BMW">
As Id is Dynamic use input[id*='bmwradio'] (Partial Match)

Selector            |          Method
[id='bmwradio']     |       Exact match
[id^='bmw']         |       Starts with "bmw"
[id$='radio']       |       Ends with "radio"
[id*='bmwradio']    |       Contains "bmwradio"